{"name": "zope-sequencesort", "metadata": {"name": "zope.sequencesort", "version": "5.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Zope :: 3", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: Zope Public License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP"], "home_page": "https://github.com/zopefoundation/zope.sequencesort", "license": "ZPL 2.1", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["setuptools"], "summary": "Sequence Sorting", "upload_time": 1674114906}, "documentation": ["# zope.sequencesort\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/zope.sequencesort.svg\n:alt: Latest Version\n:target: https://pypi.org/project/zope.sequencesort/\n```\n\n```{image} https://github.com/zopefoundation/zope.sequencesort/actions/workflows/tests.yml/badge.svg\n:target: https://github.com/zopefoundation/zope.sequencesort/actions/workflows/tests.yml\n```\n\n```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/zopesequencesort/badge/?version=latest\n:alt: Documentation Status\n:target: https://zopesequencesort.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest\n```\n\n```{image} https://coveralls.io/repos/github/zopefoundation/zope.sequencesort/badge.svg\n:target: https://coveralls.io/github/zopefoundation/zope.sequencesort\n```\n\nThis package provides support for sorting sequences based on multiple\nkeys, including locale-based comparisons and per-key directions.\n\n# Changelog\n\n## 5.0 (2023-01-19)\n\n- Add support for Python 3.11.\n- Drop support for Python 2.7, 3.5, 3.6.\n- Drop support for deprecated `python setup.py test`.\n\n## 4.2 (2021-11-04)\n\n- Fix a TypeError exception in `cmp` when operands are `None`.\n  See [issue 7](https://github.com/zopefoundation/zope.sequencesort/issues/7).\n- Drop support for Python 3.4.\n- Add support for Python 3.8, 3.9 and 3.10.\n\n## 4.1.2 (2018-10-10)\n\n- Fix regression introduced in 4.1.1 where two `_Smallest` objects are no\n  longer considered to be equal.\n\n## 4.1.1 (2018-10-05)\n\n- Handle sorting of broken objects more gracefully.\n  ([#4](https://github.com/zopefoundation/zope.sequencesort/pull/4))\n\n## 4.1.0 (2018-08-13)\n\n- Updated `boostrap.py` to version 2.2.\n- Drop support for Python 2.6, 3.2 and 3.3.\n- Add support for Python 3.4, 3.5, 3.6 and 3.7.\n- The locale comparison functions, `strcoll` and `strcoll_nocase`\n  are always available, not only if the `locale` module had been\n  imported before this module.\n\n## 4.0.1 (2013-03-04)\n\n- Fix omitted tests under Py3k.\n\n## 4.0.0 (2013-02-28)\n\n- Added `setup.py docs` alias (installs `Sphinx` and dependencies).\n- Added `setup.py dev` alias (runs `setup.py develop` plus installs\n  `nose` and `coverage`).\n- Dropped spurious `test` extra requirement on `zope.testing`.\n- 100% unit test coverage.\n- Added support for PyPy, Python 3.2 / 3.2.\n- Dropped support for Python 2.4 / 2.5.\n\n## 3.4.0 (2007-10-03)\n\n- Initial release independent of the main Zope3 tree.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "zope.sequencesort.tests", "documentation": ["Python package."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort", "documentation": ["#############################################################################", "Copyright (c) 2002 Zope Foundation and Contributors.", "This software is subject to the provisions of the Zope Public License,", "Version 2.1 (ZPL).  A copy of the ZPL should accompany this distribution.", "THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\" AND ANY AND ALL EXPRESS OR IMPLIED", "WARRANTIES ARE DISCLAIMED, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, THE IMPLIED", "WARRANTIES OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, AGAINST INFRINGEMENT, AND FITNESS", "FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE", "#############################################################################"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "zope.sequencesort.sort", "xref": {"fqname": "zope.sequencesort.ssort.sort", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort", "documentation": ["Advanced sort support\n\ne.g .Sort(sequence, ((\"akey\", \"nocase\"), (\"anotherkey\", \"cmp\", \"desc\")))", "#############################################################################", "Copyright (c) 2002 Zope Foundation and Contributors.", "This software is subject to the provisions of the Zope Public License,", "Version 2.1 (ZPL).  A copy of the ZPL should accompany this distribution.", "THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\" AND ANY AND ALL EXPRESS OR IMPLIED", "WARRANTIES ARE DISCLAIMED, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, THE IMPLIED", "WARRANTIES OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, AGAINST INFRINGEMENT, AND FITNESS", "FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE", "#############################################################################"], "functions": [{"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort.cmp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "lhs", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rhs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort.sort", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sequence", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sort", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "_", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "mapping", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a sorted copy of 'sequence'.\n\n```\nparam sequence\n\nis a sequence of objects to be sorted\n\nparam sort\n\nis a sequence of tuples (key,func,direction)\nthat define the sort order:\n\nkey is the name of an attribute to sort the objects by\n\nfunc is the name of a comparison function. This parameter is\noptional\n\nallowed values:\n\n\"cmp\" -- the standard comparison function (default)\n\n\"nocase\" -- case-insensitive comparison\n\n\"strcoll\" or \"locale\" -- locale-aware string comparison\n\n\"strcoll_nocase\" or \"locale_nocase\" -- locale-aware case-insensitive\n\nstring comparison\n\n\"xxx\" -- a user-defined comparison function\n\ndirection defines the sort direction for the key (optional).\n(allowed values: \"asc\" (default) , \"desc\")\n```\n"]}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort.nocase", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "str1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "str2", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort.strcoll_nocase", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "str1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "str2", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort.make_sortfunctions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sortfields", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Accepts a list of sort fields; splits every field, finds comparison\nfunction. Returns a list of 3-tuples (field, cmp_function, asc_multplier)"]}], "variables": [{"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort._Smallest", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort.SortEx", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort.BASIC_TYPES", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort._SORT_FUNCTIONS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort._Smallest", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "zope.sequencesort.ssort._Smallest.__lt__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"